+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+This remediation followed the exported review threads in `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` as the source of truth. All five visible threads were classified before any code edits. The authoritative classification is recorded in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+## Code and Doc Changes
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+  Normalizes the incoming approval state before calling `build_preview_payload`, so `manual_review` consistently becomes `human_review_required` for both live and fallback preview responses.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`
+  Preserves `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the fallback `preview_unavailable` payload instead of dropping them when `preview_enabled` is `false`.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`
+  Extends the writable regression surface to cover both the direct fallback payload and the router path with `approval_state="manual_review"` plus `preview_enabled=False`.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`
+  Updates the fallback JSON example to show the corrected payload with `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
+
+## Explicit Non-Changes
+
+- Did not apply `T-214-03`; the suggestion was obsolete and would have reintroduced legacy preview branching.
+- Did not add `legacy_preview_hint`.
+- Did not modify any prohibited files, including `.github/review_export/`, `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md`, or `tests/test_approval_router.py`.
+
+## Verification
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests/test_preview.py
+python3 -m unittest tests/test_approval_router.py
+```
+
+Result:
+
+- `tests/test_preview.py`: 3 tests passed
+- `tests/test_approval_router.py`: 2 tests passed
+
+The verified behavior now satisfies the required fallback case:
+
+`build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`
+
+returns a payload that keeps:
+
+- `approval_state = "human_review_required"`
+- `requires_human_review = true`
