+# PR-214 Reply Draft
+
+## T-214-01
+
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`. The router now normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before building the payload, and the fallback response keeps both `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` when `preview_enabled` is `false`.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. This was the same reopened fallback payload regression, so the fix for `T-214-01` covers it without a separate code path.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Marked obsolete. The suggestion points at an outdated diff hunk and would revive legacy preview branching on the current branch, so it was intentionally not applied.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Addressed in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added a regression test that exercises `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)` and asserts the fallback payload preserves `approval_state="human_review_required"` with `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example matches the fixed payload and explicitly documents `approval_state` plus `requires_human_review`.
